rComments: Orgo is a difficult subject, but Dalili tries her hardest to make it interesting, by providing real-life applications for the reactions learnt in class and walking us through lots of examples. She also offers lots of extra credit opportunities. I still had to work my butt off for this course, but at least with Dalili, it was a bit more tolerable...
All the lab materials were super confusing. It was so hard to understand the lab manual.

Not only were her lectures great, but she answers questions very well both during and outside of class. She gave students the opportunity to earn extra credit. She also had very fair tests, though the final exam dropped our marks pretty badly because of the high class average.

Her teaching was mediocre at best. She forced TopHat on students (which was completely unnecessary), and forced us to buy an expensive textbook. Obviously, it is known that profs get incentives from TopHat for forcing TopHat on their students, and it didn't surprise me that someone like Dalili would exhibit such money grubbing behaviour.
Amazing prof. Great lectures and easy midterms. Tough final but doable with practice. Gives you alot of bonus/extra marks for random things like surveys. Would 100% take again
Prof. Dalili is extremely knowledgeable and explains concepts really well. She also brings in visual aid which helps a lot, there are also LOADS of practice to do to ensure you pass the course.

Shadi is an amazing lecturer. She knows the content well and can articulate it quite clearly. However, organic chem overall is quite difficult, memorizing all the mechanisms and such, so if you take this course make sure its Shadi teaching. She gave many extra credit opportunities and had a lot of office hours which I appreciated
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'EXTRA CREDIT', 'Participation matters']

rComments: She seemed a little rude at first but she really does care about her students. Do all of the Tophat practice questions because not only are they a part of your mark, but they often show up on her exams. Try to get higher marks on your midterms because her final is significantly harder. Go to class because she is great at explaining concepts!!

Great prof, but hard content. Lots of resources available to do well in the course if you put in the effort. She made herself available several times during the week in her office or via online chatting mechanisms. Lab component was tedious but very enjoyable. Show up to class, read the textbook, and do practice problems if you want an A.

She's such a nice prof and is so good at explaining concepts. She goes over a ton of practice problems in class, and her mark breakdown is sweet! You get so many chances to make up for marks through extra cred projects, participation marks, etc. Her midterms are easy if you do her extra practice problems but final is kinda hard, but totally doable

Honestly one of the best profs at UTSC. She is always willing to help her students and you can tell she cares for her students. She is always has amazing lectures and definitely knows her concepts. Would take again although her final exam is pretty hard in my opinion.
One of the best profs I've ever had at UTSC. She explains the material so clearly and really cares for her students. Would highly recommend taking any course that she's teaching.
CHOOSE HER IF YOU CAN!

Amazing Prof! she is so sweet and helps you whenever you're having trouble. She explains everything clearly. Midterms are super easy, final was a bit harder but still pretty decent. Miss having her as a prof.

She is a great professor, really cares for her students and the effort she puts in is evident in the lectures. As long as you do attend and understand the lectures and do the textbook practice questions, her extra problems, and the review session questions you can get an 80%. Need to be on top of your stuff through and then you should be fine.
The best professor I have met so far :D

She is one of the best instructors I have ever had. Really approachable and supportive. She provides a lot of resources to make the concepts clear. Really knows her concepts. Would definitely love to take a course with her again.

She's great at explaining, and actually I'd never knew that I would like and have fun studying for organic chemistry so much. She makes you enjoy what you do. No need the book just attend her lecture, understand and practice; and you'll do good.

The class isn't very hard if you break it up into chunks. She gives you a lot of chances to get free marks and the exams aren't too bad. The person who said you don't need to study is either bsing or a genius. The class requires studying but if you study a little at a time you can get an A.

Professor Dalili is simply AMAZING. Chemistry has never ever been so crystal clear and interesting. She is extremely intelligent and loves to help students. I HIGHLY recommend this professor, she is a genius.
woo hoo, i <3 dalili because the final was bell curved.

teaches concepts very well, her mark breakdown is the most generous i believe of any second science course. Marks given for participation and online homework. Midterms and finals are very simple and do not require much studying as long as you understand concepts. Basically impossible to fail class and easiest chem course to get an A in
easy midterms, labs, ace organic, and attendance.but really hard final.

Simple, easy and clear. She doesn't read off slides. She knows her material well. Best chem prof to date.Some people don't like her because they got owned by the midterm, but that's their fault because her midterm is straight forward and if you do the assigned questions, its a piece of cake.
Easy Lab Easy Midterm ABSOLUTELY IMPOSSIBLE FINAL!
Shes less approachable then Verner
Very helpful, great at explaining difficult concepts, is aware of common struggles and takes extra time in those areas. Great professor!
Extremely helpful and knowledgable prof! She knows her stuff really well. Although her exams are challenging and drain your brain but they are fair! I would highly recommend this prof.

Her midterm was easy, but the final is killer. However, neither was unexpected. We were given past finals/midterms which were similar in question style. She is very helpful, and lectures well. Lots of extrahelp available. Do the homework. Study. Ask for help. Do AceOrg without cheating. Do practice exams without looking at solutions first. Get A+.

Her lecture slides are great study notes and she explains concepts very clearly. Make sure you listen in class, take notes and practice questions. I liked her better than Verner but I liked Verner's exams better (because they are easier).
i had her first year when it was her first time teaching she was by far my worst prof.
Good prof, extensive knowledge, very approachable. Study hard for her exam, it's not like Verner.
so boring it hurts, good for insomniacs
Don't bother asking her for much, she's too stuck up. Speaks too fast. UTSC can hire better profs.

lol, she's fine as a professor, although i do prefer ann verner's classes. i guess we should all have learned that we can't only rely on the lectures as the only source of learning now. for me i'm fine with her pace.
